==English==
===Etymology===
See the Wikipedia article [[w:ISO 216|ISO 216]], the international standard on paper sizes.

===Noun===
'''A5'''
# A standard [[paper]] size, defined by ISO 216.
#: dimensions: 210 x 149 mm  (210.224 x 148.651 mm)
# The fifth address register on [[Motorola]] [[68k]] processors.

===Adjective===
'''A5'''
# of that size
#:  ''a sheet of '''A5''' paper''

